column1: This is a Human Adjudicated GT for a set of anonymized emails---suspected scam/impersonation emails collected by Panacea team members---wherein each row consists of an email number (1 is the first email in the pool), a sentence from that email, a potential Ask or Framing action (e.g., "contact", "win"), arguments of that action, confidence score associated with Ask or Framing (if there is one), the Ask (e.g., "contact"=PERFORM), the Framing (e.g., "win"=GAIN), an Ask or Framing structure (including URL).  If there is an Ask, the designation as Top Ask is marked X if it is a top ask (or unmarked if not), and an Ask Category is provided. Potential Asks and Framings are extracted using dependency/constituency parsing and semantic role labeling (SRL). Experimental data associated with this Ground truth are available on the Ask Detection website. Note: The Case Index in GT is aligned with the Case Index in the Experimental Data. Also, see Dorr et al., AAAI 2020 for overall Precision, Recall, and F results based on these outcomes.
